# Custom Embedded Linux with Buildroot

A minimal custom Linux image built from scratch using Buildroot, targeting ARM architecture and booted on QEMU emulator. Includes a custom init script, SSH access via Dropbear, and a fully assembled root filesystem.

---

## What This Project Does

- Builds a complete Linux system from source using Buildroot
- Cross-compiles everything for ARM (armv7l) on an x86-64 host machine
- Boots the image on a QEMU ARM VExpress emulator
- Runs a custom init script at boot
- Exposes SSH access via Dropbear

---

## System Overview

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| Build system | Buildroot 2024.02 |
| Target architecture | ARM (armv7l) |
| Board | QEMU VExpress-A9 |
| Kernel | Linux 6.1.44 |
| Init system | BusyBox init |
| SSH server | Dropbear |
| Host machine | Ubuntu 22.04 (x86-64) |

---

## Boot Sequence

```text
QEMU (emulates ARM hardware)
  └── Linux kernel (zImage)
        └── Mounts rootfs (rootfs.ext2)
              └── BusyBox init (PID 1)
                    └── Runs /etc/init.d/S99hello (custom script)
                          └── Starts Dropbear SSH server
```

---

## Project Structure

```text
buildroot/
├── .config
└── board/
    └── raspberrypi/
        └── rootfs_overlay/
            └── etc/
                └── init.d/
                    └── S99hello
```

---

## Custom Init Script

Located at `board/raspberrypi/rootfs_overlay/etc/init.d/S99hello`

```sh
#!/bin/sh

case "$1" in
  start)
    echo "Hello from my custom init script" > /dev/console
    ;;
  stop)
    echo "Stopping" > /dev/console
    ;;
esac
```

BusyBox init runs all scripts in `/etc/init.d/` at boot. Scripts prefixed with `S` are start scripts. `99` means this runs last, after all other services are up.

---

## How to Build

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
sudo apt install -y build-essential git wget unzip bc cpio \
  libncurses-dev libssl-dev rsync file python3 qemu-utils
```

### 2. Clone Buildroot

```bash
git clone https://git.buildroot.net/buildroot --depth=1 --branch 2024.02 ~/buildroot
cd ~/buildroot
```

### 3. Load config

```bash
make qemu_arm_vexpress_defconfig
```

### 4. Configure

```bash
make menuconfig
```

Changes made:

- `Target packages → Networking applications → dropbear [*]`
- `System configuration → Root password → <your password>`
- `System configuration → Root filesystem overlay → board/raspberrypi/rootfs_overlay`

### 5. Build

```bash
make -j$(nproc)
```

Output files will be generated in:

```text
output/images/
```

---

## How to Run

```bash
cd output/images

qemu-system-arm -M vexpress-a9 -smp 1 -m 256 \
  -kernel zImage \
  -dtb vexpress-v2p-ca9.dtb \
  -drive file=rootfs.ext2,if=sd,format=raw \
  -append "console=ttyAMA0,115200 rootwait root=/dev/mmcblk0" \
  -nographic \
  -netdev user,id=net0,hostfwd=tcp::2222-:22 \
  -device virtio-net-device,netdev=net0
```

Login with:

```text
Username: root
Password: <password set in menuconfig>
```

---

## SSH Access

Open a new terminal on the host machine:

```bash
ssh root@localhost -p 2222
```

